<geoCoordinate box="[789,856,1569,1595]" degrees="24" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="24.0">24º N</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate box="[893,963,1569,1595]" degrees="40" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="40.0">40º N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[975,1048,1569,1595]" degrees="50" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="-50.0">50º W</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate box="[1086,1159,1569,1595]" degrees="76" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="-76.0">76º W</geoCoordinate>
(
<figureCitation box="[1175,1291,1569,1595]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="53.[151,255,735,759]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,391,713]" captionTargetId="figure-639@53.[153,1438,381,717]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURE 23. Map of distribution of (A) Pseudoscopelus aphos (diamond), P. lavenbergi (cross), and P. parini (circle); (B) P. astronesthidens (cross), P. australis (asterisk), and P. odontoglossum (star). Each symbol may represent more than one locality; solid symbols represent type localities." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6031466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6031466/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 23 A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" box="[198,1185,1608,1635]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,517,1608,1634]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Bathymetric distribution.</emphasis>
Meso- to bathypelagic, from 
<quantity box="[865,1036,1609,1635]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.27" metricValueMax="16.34" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="927.0" valueMax="1634.0" valueMin="220.0">220 to 1634 m</quantity>
(mean 667).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1649,1675]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Prokofiev and Kukuev" box="[331,694,1650,1676]" firstAuthor="Prokofiev" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="712 - 729" refId="ref59420" refString="Prokofiev, A. M. &amp; Kukuev, E. I. (2005) Preliminary review of the Atlantic linebellies of the genus Pseudoscopelus with remarks on the species composition of the genus in the world's fauna (Perciformes, Chiasmodontidae). I. Voprosy Ikhtyologii, 45, 749 - 767 (in Russian, English translation Journal of Ichthyology, 45, 712 - 729)." type="journal article" year="2005">Prokofiev and Kukuev (2005)</bibRefCitation>
presented an erroneous description of color. They based the description on a poorly preserved specimen, which was collected in 1977 and kept in formalin since then; the bones were uncalcified and the overall color was faded to brown, typical of museum specimens. They described the color of internal area of mouth as black; in fact there are some melanophores on the skin of premaxilla and dentary, especially on dentigerous areas and on basibranchials, which gives a dusky aspect.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" lastBlockId="50.[151,1435,152,218]" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
The data presented herein is based on a reasonable amount of specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[1173,1223,1852,1878]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">type</typeStatus>
locality and adjacent areas. Some specimens are in great shape and have well-preserved pigmentation allowing this to be a more accurate description. The internal areas of mouth and gill arches are demonstrated in 
<figureCitation box="[1233,1378,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="41.[151,255,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,860,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-288@41.[151,1436,859,1797]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 19. Pseudoscopelus paxtoni: (A) NMNZ P. 28657, 205.1 mm, holotype; (B) MNMZ P. 37858, 200.4 mm, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6031454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6031454/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figure 19 B</figureCitation>
; it is not as back as described. Based on such mistake, 
<bibRefCitation author="Prokofiev and Kukuev" box="[746,1102,1973,1999]" firstAuthor="Prokofiev" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref59719" refString="Prokofiev, A. M. &amp; Kukuev, E. I. (2008) Systematics and Distribution of the swallowerfishes of the genus Pseudoscopelus (Chiasmodontidae). KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow, 162 p." type="book" year="2008">Prokofiev and Kukuev (2008)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosed 
